25|$|One of main, and {{the best}} known, {{filtration}} camps in Chechnya was the Chernokozovo detention center, {{set up in a}} former prison in 1999. Chernokozovo was subject of a significant attention in 2000, as well as at least two illegal detention and torture related rulings by the European Court of Human Rights (the cases of the Chitayev brothers in 2007 and of Zura Bitiyeva in 2008, the latter also including the subsequent <b>summary</b> <b>execution</b> of her and her family).|$|E
25|$|The Horsa {{was first}} {{deployed}} operationally {{on the night}} of 19/20 November 1942 in the unsuccessful attack on the German Heavy Water Plant at Rjukan in Norway (Operation Freshman). The two Horsa gliders, each carrying 15 sappers, and one of the Halifax tug aircraft crashed in Norway due to bad weather. All 23 survivors from the glider crashes were executed on the orders of Adolf Hitler, in a flagrant breach of the Geneva Convention which protects prisoners of war (POWs) from <b>summary</b> <b>execution.</b>|$|E
